Government bumps up supply of private homes for full-year 2023 to highest in decade:Source1. TO CATER to strong private residential demand  the government is further increasing the supply of private homes on the confirmed list to about 5 160 units – including 560 executive condominium (EC) units – in the second half of this year. This is 26.2 per cent higher than the supply of 4 090 private homes (including 700 EC units) in the current  first-half 2023 Government Land Sales (GLS) programme.2. The Ministry of National Development (MND) on Wednesday (Jun 21) also said that the total confirmed list supply of 9 250 units for full-year 2023 is at the highest level since 2013. This is also nearly 50 per cent higher than the supply in 2022  and around 2.5 times the supply in 2021.3.
